Avid Larizadeh-Duggan (born 1978 or 1979) is an Iranian-French-American entrepreneur and venture capitalist. She is a general partner at Google Ventures and co-founded online accessories company Boticca, acquired by Wolf and Badger.
She is a Mayfield Fellow and a Kauffman Fellow. In 2016 she was named one of the World Economic Forum's "Young Global Leaders".
